<TITLE> Nalbandian recovers, will join Argentine team in Sweden </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BUENOS AIRES, March 4 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - David Nalbandian has recovered from a leg muscle tear and left for Stockholm on Wednesday to join Argentina's Davis Cup team to face Sweden, the Argentine Tennis Association (AAT) said. "Captain Modesto Vazquez and vice-captain Ricardo Rivera confirmed ... that Nalbandian will be in Sweden for the Davis Cup," the AAT said in a statement. Nalbandian was injured two weeks ago during the Buenos Aires Open, his comeback tournament from hip surgery last May, and pulled out of the world group, first round tie. However, having recovered he is joining the Argentine team who have lost U.S. Open champion Juan Martin del Potro and world number 27 Juan Monaco to injury. "Nalbandian will be included in the team in place of Federico Del Bonis," the statement said referring to the 19-year-old called up last weekend after Monaco was injured
